<item>
            <title>[LU-12121] DOM: BRW to missing obj?</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12121</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From time to time, I can see BRW to missing obj error on MDTs with DOM:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;fir-md1-s2: Mar 26 10:45:33 fir-md1-s2 kernel: LustreError: 90902:0:(mdt_io.c:442:mdt_preprw_write()) fir-MDT0003: BRW to missing obj [0x28000f666:0xca48:0x0]
fir-md1-s2: Mar 26 10:48:36 fir-md1-s2 kernel: LustreError: 91887:0:(mdt_io.c:442:mdt_preprw_write()) fir-MDT0003: BRW to missing obj [0x28000f7a6:0x1bfa:0x0]
fir-md1-s2: Mar 26 10:48:38 fir-md1-s2 kernel: LustreError: 91726:0:(mdt_io.c:442:mdt_preprw_write()) fir-MDT0003: BRW to missing obj [0x28000f666:0xd1a1:0x0]
fir-md1-s2: Mar 26 10:49:05 fir-md1-s2 kernel: LustreError: 91846:0:(mdt_io.c:442:mdt_preprw_write()) fir-MDT0003: BRW to missing obj [0x28000f52a:0x98bf:0x0]
fir-md1-s2: Mar 26 10:53:48 fir-md1-s2 kernel: LustreError: 91423:0:(mdt_io.c:442:mdt_preprw_write()) fir-MDT0003: BRW to missing obj [0x28000f7bb:0x6d61:0x0]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any idea of what is causing this, is it just a warning? Note: we haven&apos;t noticed any real issue, I am just wondering.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;br/&gt;
Stephane&lt;/p&gt;</description>
